# Project Context

This repository is **Building a Personal AI Cloud** — an O'Reilly-style technical book published with **Docusaurus**, not a flat Markdown repo or application codebase.

## What We Are Building

A hands-on book that teaches cloud engineering by building infrastructure to run **[Hermes Agent](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent)** (Nous Research) on AWS → Docker → k3s → production.

**Platform focus (mandatory):**
- All narrative, labs, and architecture are **Hermes-centric** — product = hermes-agent, not a custom agent
- Real-world usage scenarios: `docs/appendices/hermes-cookbook.md`
- **ULLR** may appear only as an optional data backend Hermes integrates with — never as the primary product or chapter subject
- Frame capstones as: *what does the Hermes agent need?*

