## Technical Defaults

- **AWS home region:** `us-west-2` (Oregon); AZ example `us-west-2a`; subnet name `hermes-public-usw2a`
- **OS on EC2:** Ubuntu Server LTS (user `ubuntu`)
- **Orchestration target:** k3s on EC2
- **IaC:** Terraform (Part V)
- **Local inference:** **llama.cpp** (`llama-server` Helm chart)—not Ollama. GGUF on `/models`, HTTP `/completion` API, cluster-internal only.
- **Published site:** https://crudnicky.github.io/agent-to-aws-guide/

## Writing Workflow (RFC)

1. Outline → 2. Review → 3. Expand sections → 4. Diagrams → 5. Lab (tested) → 6. Troubleshooting → 7. Glossary/refs → 8. Edit → 9. Mark done in SUMMARY.md

Every chapter must answer: (1) what problem, (2) why invented, (3) how it works internally, (4) how to use it in *your* infrastructure.

## CI Requirements

PRs must pass: markdownlint, `code/scripts/ci/validate-links.sh`, `npm run build` (Docusaurus throws on broken links).

Preview locally: `npm start`

## Git / Commits

- Do **not** commit unless the user explicitly asks
- One branch per chapter: `chapter-NN-slug`
- Commit format: `chNN: description`

## AI Behavior

- Prefer **why before how** — not command memorization lists
- Match existing chapter voice (second person, present tense)
- Minimize scope — don't refactor unrelated files
- When editing chapters, follow `STYLE_GUIDE.md` section order exactly
- Cross-link with relative paths: `[Chapter 9](../part-ii-aws/09-provisioning-hermes-server.md)`
